 legacy of porcelain export and current networks of exchange, Burchmore ultimately demonstrates why this ceramic practice is crucial to understanding the development of Chinese contemporary art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aArt, Chinesey21st century. 0aPorcelainxSocial aspectsy21st centuryvCase studies. 7aART / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520392571?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520392571423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520392571/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPKb2023